# Part 1 — Tidiness

---

## 1. Do you like to keep things tidy?

Yes, I do. I’m the kind of person who feels more comfortable and productive in a clean and organized environment. For example, when my desk is messy, I find it difficult to concentrate because I get distracted easily. On the other hand, a tidy space helps me think more clearly and manage my time better. I wouldn’t say I’m obsessed with cleanliness, but I definitely prefer things to be well-organized rather than chaotic.

### 中文翻译：

是的，我喜欢保持整洁。我属于那种在干净、有条理的环境里会更舒服、更高效的人。比如说，当我的书桌很乱的时候，我会很难集中注意力，因为特别容易分心。相反，一个整洁的环境能让我思路更清晰，也更容易安排时间。当然，我并不是有洁癖，但我确实更喜欢有秩序而不是乱糟糟的环境。

---

## 2. Did you use to keep your room tidy as a child?

Not really, to be honest. When I was a child, my room was usually full of toys, books, and random things scattered everywhere. My parents often reminded me to clean it up, but I didn’t really care at that age. However, as I grew older, especially after becoming a university student, I realized that tidiness actually affects my mood and efficiency. So compared with the past, I’m much more organized now.

### 中文翻译：

老实说，其实没有。我小时候的房间经常到处都是玩具、书和各种杂物。我父母经常提醒我整理，但那个年纪我并不太在意。不过随着年龄增长，尤其是上大学之后，我意识到整洁其实会影响我的情绪和学习效率。所以相比以前，我现在有条理多了。

---

## 3. How do you keep your work or study space tidy?

I usually try to clean my desk at the end of each day instead of letting the mess build up. I separate books, notebooks, and electronic devices into different areas so I can find things quickly. Since I study computer science, I also organize my digital files carefully, because a messy computer desktop can be just as distracting as a messy room. Besides that, I throw away unnecessary papers regularly, which helps keep my study area simple and efficient.

### 中文翻译：

我通常会在每天结束时整理一下书桌，而不是让杂乱不断堆积。我会把书、本子和电子设备分开放，这样找东西会更快。因为我是学计算机的，所以我也会认真整理电脑里的文件，因为杂乱的电脑桌面其实和凌乱的房间一样容易让人分心。此外，我会定期清理没用的纸张，这样学习区域会显得更简洁、更高效。

---

## 4. Do you think that it is necessary to be tidy?

Yes, I think it’s quite important, especially in modern life where people already face a lot of stress and distractions. A tidy environment can improve concentration, reduce anxiety, and even save time because you don’t waste energy looking for things. Of course, people don’t need to keep everything perfect all the time, but having basic organization skills is definitely beneficial. In my opinion, tidiness reflects self-discipline to some extent.

### 中文翻译：

是的，我觉得整洁很重要，尤其是在现代生活中，人们本来就面临很多压力和干扰。一个整洁的环境能够提高专注力、减少焦虑，甚至节省时间，因为你不用总是花时间找东西。当然，人们也没必要时时刻刻都保持完美，但拥有基本的整理习惯绝对是有好处的。在我看来，整洁在某种程度上也体现了一个人的自律能力。
